UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.Compressor Se: Determines how much to adjust the dynamic range of the signal. A "Hard" setting will more aggressively turn down loud sounds and turn up the quiet sounds.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.SFX Ducking.D: Determines how much to reduce the volume of sound effects while the speaker is playing.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.AllowPortSele: Determines if the Patchwork Tool can access any cable input or output ports on the device.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.PlayAtLocatio: Determines if the audio should be played from the device location or any registered players' locations.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.EnabledOnPhas: Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. Pre-game includes all phases prior to start of game (like the pre-game lobby or countdown to start of game.) This setting does not affect Edit Mode.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.MusicEventGro: Determines which speakers can be heard at the same time.
Determines who will be able to hear the sound played from this speaker.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.Disable.Descr: Disables the device when an event occurs.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.Enable.Descri: Enables the device when an event occurs.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.LegalInfo.Des: Please note: Use of a Patchwork audio device is limited to the creation of new and original musical works.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.RegisterPlaye: Registers the instigating player as a target for the speaker.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.UnregisterAll: Removes all registered players as targets for the speaker.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.UnregisterPla: Removes the instigating player as a target for the speaker.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.AudioSpatiali: Sets the distance beyond the Full Volume Distance over which the speaker's audio gradually becomes silent.
Sets the distance from the speaker where its audio is heard at full volume. Setting this to "Full Island" will play the audio at full volume regardless of distance from the speaker.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.AudioIn.Descr: Sets the inputs for this device's Audio In port.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.VolumeIn.Desc: Sets the inputs for this device's Volume knob.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.Volume.Descri: Sets the volume of the speaker.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.OnDisabled.De: Triggers an event when the device is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.OnEnabled.Des: Triggers an event when the device is enabled.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.VisibleInGame: When set to OFF, hides the speaker in Play mode. This allows it to be positioned as needed for spatial audio without players being able to see it.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.FadeInTime.De: When this device becomes audible to a player, determines the time in seconds it takes to ramp to its set volume from 0.
UserOptionDefinition.BP_Device_ModularEmitter_C.FadeOutTime.D: When this device ceases to be audible to a player, determines the time in seconds it takes to ramp from its set volume to 0.
